Package: ipython-py22
Version: 0.5.0
Revision: 10
Maintainer: Andrea Riciputi <ariciputi@users.sourceforge.net>
Depends: python22
Recommends: gnuplot, gnuplot-py22, numeric-py22
Conflicts: ipython
Replaces: ipython
Source: http://ipython.scipy.org/dist/IPython-%v.tar.gz 
Source-MD5: 134ccdb03a4094f991def74230137b21
CompileScript: python2.2 setup.py build
InstallScript: <<
 python2.2 setup.py install --prefix=%i
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n
 cp -R %i/share/doc/IPython/* %i/share/doc/%n
 rm -R %i/share/doc/IPython

 mv %i/bin/ipython %i/bin/ipython2.2
 mv %i/bin/pycolor %i/bin/pycolor2.2

 mv %i/share/man/man1/ipython.1.gz %i/share/man/man1/ipython-py22.1.gz
 mv %i/share/man/man1/pycolor.1.gz %i/share/man/man1/pycolor-py22.1.gz
<<
DocFiles: README README_Windows.txt PKG-INFO
Description: Replacement interactive Python interpreter 
DescDetail: <<
 A replacement for the interactive Python interpreter with extra functionality.

 Maintainer's note: With version 0.5.0 the problem with Apple Terminal seems fixed. 
 Let me know any terminal misbehavior.
<<
PostInstScript: <<
 update-alternatives --install %p/bin/ipython ipython %p/bin/ipython2.2 50 --slave %p/share/man/man1/ipython.1.gz ipython.1.gz %p/share/man/man1/ipython-py22.1.gz
 update-alternatives --install %p/bin/pycolor pycolor %p/bin/pycolor2.2 50 --slave %p/share/man/man1/pycolor.1.gz pycolor.1.gz %p/share/man/man1/pycolor-py22.1.gz

 echo ""
 echo " With version 0.5.0 the problem with Apple Terminal seems fixed."
 echo " Setting TERM to xterm seems to be unnecessary."
 echo " Let me know any terminal misbehavior."
 echo ""
 echo "Actually '%p/bin/ipython' is a symlink automatically updated by the"
 echo "update-alternatives utility. If you install both ipython-py22 and "
 echo "ipython-py23 the symlink will point to 2.2 version by default."
<<
PreRmScript: <<
 if [ $1 != "upgrade" ]; then
   update-alternatives --remove ipython %p/bin/ipython2.2
   update-alternatives --remove pycolor %p/bin/pycolor2.2
 fi
<<
